r_1=\frac{1}{2},x_1=1, r_n=\frac 12x_n, x_{n+1}=\sqrt 2r_n.
r_{n+1}=\frac 12 x_{n+1}=\frac 12\cdot \sqrt 2r_n=\frac{\sqrt 2}{2}r_n.
\pi\left\{\left(\frac 12\right)^2+\left(\frac{\sqrt 2}{4}\right)^2+\left(\frac{1}{4}\right)^2+\cdots\right\}=\pi\left(\frac{1}{4}+\frac{1}{8}+\frac{1}{16}+\cdots\right)=\pi\cdot\frac{1/4}{1-(1/2)}=\frac{\pi}{2}.
